result.execSummary:
The defendant Isaiah M Williams was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Felon Possess Firearm [Modifiers: Repeater, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.29(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  
*  Pay supervision fees.  
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not be in taverns or on any premises licensed for the sale of intoxicating beverages, except restaurants or grocery stores.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment.  Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program.  Obtain GED or H.S.E.D. during term of probation.  
*  Pay all court costs including all applicable surcharges.  
*  If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.  
*  Defendant is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay DNA surcharge and notice is given.  
May not associate with gangs/gang members or gang affiliations.  May not have contact with Tavia T & Demingo W, unless otherwise permitted by the court/agent.  May not possess any weapons, including firearms.

Attorney Jason Zapf appeared for the State. DE appears in custody with Atty Hilary Edwards.   Clerk P. Scypta.   
MINUTES:  1143 - Atty Edwards moves JT on 3/8 with suppression motions to be heard during the trial. ADA Zapf is not available 3/10. DA's office is also not able to effectuate subpoenas for witnesses to appear by next week. Court finds that due to circumstances beyond the control of the court, speedy trial demands cannot be met. Court therefore denies DE's motion for immediate JT for cause. Atty Edwards moves to modify bond to signature. ST requests tolling of time limits to allow continuance of cash bonds. Court grants DE's motion and modifies bond to $25K signature. All conditions are to continue. Motion hearing on suppression set. Atty Edwards renews request for discovery that she believes to still be unsatisfied from the US Marshals. ST states some of the requested materials have already been turned over. Court finds that the specific requests made for discovery for items held by the US Marshals are beyond the scope of the statute / capabilities of the ST. Therefore, the court makes no order to the ST as to DE's motion for discovery.  Motion hearing scheduled for April 28, 2016 at 09:30 am.  Status conference scheduled for May 25, 2016 at 10:00 am.

Due to unavailability of the Judge, both the Motion Hearing and JT are being rescheduled. STC set for 3/4/16 @ 11:30am. Speedy Trials and Suppression Motions to be addressed at STC. All attorneys notified by e-mail.
Due to unavailability of Judge, Motion rescheduled to 2/25 @ 2pm. Attys notified and confirmed by email. Conveyance notified.
for Suppression filed by Atty Edwards

Attorney Jason Zapf and DDA Mike Graveley appeared for the State. DE appears in custody with Atty Hilary Edwards.   Clerk P. Scypta.   
MINUTES: 1047 - Matter heard with 15CF947 (co-de). Atty Edwards will be filing a Motion to Suppress 2/12/16 and requests the Motion be heard on 2/29 - denied. Suppression motion will be heard, however it will recalibrate the Speedy Trial Demand timeline.  Atty Edwards objects to any change in the Speedy Trial Demand due to the discovery issue named in 15CF947 - modification of DE's bond also requested. DDA Graveley states that multiple contacts have been made with PPPD, and no further discovery is available - of which Atty Edwards has been made aware. PPPD had no records of any requests from DE counsel prior to 1/28. The ST, however, made the release timely. Further discussion held. Discussion held on Atty Edwards' bond motion - requests bond be reduced to $2-5K. ADA Zapf opposes any modification of bond. For reasons set forth on the record, Court finds that the bond as set is appropriate - motion to modify bond is denied. Court further finds that NO suppression motion based on the issue of discovery as set forth on the record today will be entertained.  Atty Edwards is ordered to file her Motion to Suppress no later than 2/12/16.  Motion hearing scheduled for February 22, 2016 at 02:00 pm.
